main.java.de.bsi.seapi.exceptions

Class ErrorTimeNotSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • main.java.de.bsi.seapi.exceptions.ErrorTimeNotSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class ErrorTimeNotSet
extends java.lang.Exception
    This class defines the exception ErrorTimeNotSet that is thrown if an appropriate SE API function is invoked although the managed data/time in the Secure Element has not been updated after the initialization of the SE API or a period of absence of current for the Secure Element
